Author: polycryptoblog#1173
Content: @bishop  its a promissory note with less than 9 months duration , it‚Äôs an exception in the securities law ( reves family resemblance test )

Author: polycryptoblog#1173
Content: That said, promissory notes are generally defined as securities unless they mature in 9 months or less.  (Securities Act 2(1), 3(a)(3); Exchange Act 3(a)(10)).

Author: polycryptoblog#1173
Content:
Judicial Exceptions include:

A note delivered in consumer financing; or
A note secured by a mortgage on a home; or
Any short-term note secured via a lien or assets of a small business; or
Any note evidencing a ‚Äúcharacter‚Äù loan to a bank customer; or
Short-term notes secured via assignments to accounts receivable; or
Any note which formalizes an open account debt incurred in the ordinary course of business, especially when collateral is involved.

Author: polycryptoblog#1173
Content: The last point is most pertinent

Author: polycryptoblog#1173
Content: (Not a lawyer just have researched a lot in this area and found some good resources )
